we're gathered here at a
Library, I would like to end
with a

00:37:18.870 --> 00:37:26.000
quote from the Fiddler on the
Roof: How do we keep our
balance? That I can tell you in

00:37:26.000 --> 00:37:32.230
one word, "tradition." Because
of our traditions, we have kept
our balance for many,

00:37:32.230 --> 00:37:39.070
many years. Because of our
tradition, every one of us knows
who he is and what God

00:37:39.070 --> 00:37:45.700
expects him to do. Without our
traditions, our lives would be
as shaky as a fiddler on the

00:37:45.700 --> 00:37:52.470
roof. In conclusion I want to
encourage you to use as many
resources here at the Library of

00:37:52.470 --> 00:37:59.870
Congress as I was exposed to,
but also remember the words from
Tina and Tima,

00:37:59.870 --> 00:38:05.300
listen closely to the language
